wikipedia_page.main: Sir George Beresford Craddock (7 October 1898 – 22 September 1976) was a British Conservative politician.  He was elected as Member of Parliament (MP) for Spelthorne at the 1950 general election, and held the seat until his retirement at the 1970 general election.  He should not be confused with George Craddock, the Labour politician who served as an MP at the same time.
